entries.title: Best red carpet fashion at the 2023 Golden Globe Awards
entries.description: Stars are arriving on the red carpet for the Golden Globe Awards, which return to TV screens after a year off air amid a boycott by studios and celebrities.

entries.title: Cardinal George Pell dies aged 81
entries.description: Cardinal George Pell, the most senior Catholic official to be convicted of child sex abuse before his 2020 acquittal, has died, according to his secretary. He was 81.

entries.title: Inside China's crackdown on tattoo culture
entries.description: "My behavior encroached on the physical and mental health of minors," read a court-ordered apology issued by a tattoo artist in China's Shaanxi province in September. "I am deeply aware of my mistakes," he added.

entries.title: 'No one counts the dead': Situation in key Ukrainian town 'critical' in face of massive Russian assault
CNN gets a close look at Soviet-era artillery system used by Russia and Ukraine
entries.description: Intense fighting is reported around an important mining town in Ukraine's east. CNN's Ben Wedeman visited a Ukrainian artillery unit on the front lines where soldiers use a Soviet-era artillery system to strike a building where Russian attack drones were launched from.

entries.title: A galactic merger brought a pair of supermassive black holes together
entries.description: Two supermassive black holes have been spotted feasting on cosmic materials as two galaxies in distant space merge — and are the closest to colliding black holes astronomers have ever observed.

entries.title: Lula adviser: Brazil congress attack showed 'failure' by local security forces
entries.description: Celso Amorim, foreign policy adviser to Brazil's president, tells Christiane Amanpour his country is "firmly on the road for the consolidation of democracy" after Bolsonaro supporters stormed Congress on Sunday.

entries.title: A romance author's alleged return from the dead has the indie writing community reeling
entries.description: In September 2020, fans and friends of Susan Meachen received devastating news. The romance writer's Facebook account posted a message saying she had died. A later post claimed she had taken her own life and suggested her actions were the results of online bullying by others in her thriving, close-knit online writing group.

entries.title: Former Trump Org. CFO Allen Weisselberg sentenced to 5 months in jail
'Shamefully good': Stephen Colbert reacts to Tom Hanks' new cocktail creation
entries.description: During an appearance on "The Late Show," actor Tom Hanks recreated his unusual cocktail creation with host Stephen Colbert. See how the duo react to "The Diet Cokagne," a mix of Diet Coke and champagne.

entries.title: Husband of missing woman allegedly searched 'how to dispose of a 115-pound woman's body'
Santos defends himself as Democrats file ethics complaint
entries.description: Rep. George Santos, the recently elected GOP congressman from New York who has admitted to lying about parts of his resume, defended himself and his record on Tuesday as two House Democrats filed an ethics complaint against him.

entries.title: Amid overhaul, it would be a good time for the Golden Globes to do away with gendered acting categories
entries.description: If anyone is looking for a fresh start in the new year, it's the Hollywood Foreign Press Association (HFPA).

entries.title: Meek Mill apologizes for filming a music video in Ghana's presidential palace
entries.description: Meek Mill has apologized for secretly filming a music video in Ghana's presidential palace.

entries.title: Prince Harry's tell-all rips open old wounds in the British royal family
entries.description: Prince Harry's memoir has officially hit bookstores in the United Kingdom and elsewhere around the globe. Here in London, several retail chains opened their doors at midnight to allow eager readers to grab their copies before sunrise.

entries.title: Watch how Biden reacted to reporter questions on classified documents
entries.description: President Joe Biden ignored reporters asking for a comment on the classified documents found at a private office from his time as vice president.

entries.title: 13-year-old victim pulled from rubble after Russian strike hit market
entries.description: CNN international correspondent Scott McLean reports from Ukraine's capital on recent Russian strikes that hit a market in a village close to the front line.

entries.title: See CES 2023's weirdest new technologies
entries.description: From a drone cam protecting the inside of your house to high tech makeup, Jeanne Moos has some e-highlights from the Consumer Electronics Show.

entries.title: Ukrainians insist situation in Soledar is 'under control' as Russia pounds settlement
New York man sets world record for eating at most Michelin-starred restaurants in a day
entries.description: A New York man has set a world record for eating at the most Michelin-starred restaurants in a single day.

entries.title: French workers can retire much younger than most. That's about to change
entries.description: The French government on Tuesday will propose raising the retirement age by at least two years as part of a long-delayed reform to the country's pension system that was met with huge protests by labor unions the last time it was attempted.

entries.title: Ukrainians to start training on Patriot missiles in US as soon as next week, officials say
Where to go ice skating 100 floors above New York City streets
entries.description: Those dramatic viewing platforms atop skyscrapers have been quite the rage for a long time now. But for thrill-seekers who want to do more than stand and gawk, there's something new on the horizon.

entries.title: First on CNN: Ukrainians to start training on Patriot missiles in US as soon as next week, officials say
entries.description: The Ukrainians are set to begin training on the Patriot missile system in the United States as soon as next week, two US officials familiar with the matter tell CNN.

entries.title: Federal officials say they are acting on 'thousands' of complaints related to Southwest meltdown
entries.description: Federal officials say they are acting on "thousands" of complaints by Southwest Airlines customers after its days-long holiday travel meltdown -- including complaints that Southwest is not making good on its pledge to issue refunds.

entries.title: Disney CEO Bob Iger orders workers to return to the office 4 days a week
entries.description: Disney CEO Bob Iger is clamping down on remote workers, according to CNBC.

entries.title: Iran's most powerful weapon isn't working
Musk's Twitter restores accounts of prominent election deniers two years after Jan. 6 attack
entries.description: Elon Musk's Twitter has restored the accounts of two prominent election deniers who were banned from the platform following the January 6, 2021 attack on the US Capitol.

entries.title: The Golden Globes are back and here's how to watch
entries.description: The 80th Golden Globe Awards will be presented -- and televised -- on Tuesday.

entries.title: The world's most powerful passport for 2023 revealed
entries.description: A trio of Asian passports offer their holders greater global travel freedom than those of any other countries, according to a new quarterly report released by London-based global citizenship and residence advisory firm Henley & Partners.

entries.title: Look of the Week: Hailey Bieber's 'nepo baby' slogan tee
entries.description: A punchy slogan t-shirt, papped at the right moment, can become an enduring image in our cultural history. In 2002, shortly after her public split with Justin Timberlake, Britney Spears' stepped out wearing a baby blue tee with the all caps mandate "DUMP HIM," a look which quickly became enshrined in the internet's clapback hall of fame (Etsy is filled with thousands of copy-cat t-shirts over two decades later.) Paris Hilton, too, was long immortalized as a meme after wearing an apparently-inflammatory black and white vest with the slogan  "Stop being poor!" in 2005 — in 2021 Hilton proved the image was doctored, however, with the actual text reading "Stop being desperate!" More recently, ahead of the release of her fifth studio album "Crash," musician Charli XCX pre-empted negative reviews by wearing a pastel pink crop top that said "They don't build statues of critics." Primarily a vehicle for sassy responses to low-brow drama, the slogan tee is a mouthpiece for the wearer — saying the quiet part out loud in a way that avoids direct responsibility.

entries.title: 'Certainly a possibility' mother could face charges after her 6-year-old allegedly shot Virginia teacher, police chief says
entries.description: The mother of a 6-year-old boy who authorities say shot his teacher at a Virginia elementary school could face charges, Newport News police Chief Steve Drew said Tuesday.

entries.title: Two global recessions in one decade? That hasn't happened in over 80 years
entries.description: The global economy is just one more knock away from a second recession in the same decade, something that hasn't happened in more than 80 years.

entries.title: 'The Last of Us' bucks the game-to-screen trend, breathing life into the zombie drama
entries.description: The spotty track record of videogame adaptations and glut of apocalyptic/zombie dramas receive a welcome boost from "The Last of Us," which proves there's room for more of each as long as it's this good. A road series with mini-dramas baked into the episodes, the HBO show quickly proves itself worthy of the hype and anticipation by delivering a fully realized series graced with flesh-and-blood characters.

entries.title: Molson Coors is launching its first-ever zero-proof cocktail
entries.description: Molson Coors is typically known for its lineup of beers and booze, but its newest drink isn't either.

entries.title: New study shows walking this way burns just as much energy as jogging
entries.description: Arizona State University professor Glenn Gaesser loves Monty Python so much, he researched the possible health benefits of one of their funniest skits. The positive results caught him off guard, "It took me half a century to come to this, all right!?"

entries.title: Most teens have seen porn online by age 12. Here is how to talk to them
entries.description: Families waiting to talk about pornography until their children are teenagers should move up that schedule, according to a new report.

entries.title: Bruised tech investors are hedging their bets
entries.description: There are two certainties in today's market: The tech sector has been beaten down and interest rates are higher.

entries.title: US made 'substantive' change in weaponry for Ukraine: officials
entries.description: There has been a "substantive" change in the type of weaponry the US and its allies are providing to Ukraine to meet Kyiv's requests for firepower, two senior US officials tells CNN.

entries.title: Satellite images capture crowding at China's crematoriums and funeral homes as Covid surge continues
entries.description: Satellite images taken over a number of Chinese cities have captured crowding at crematoriums and funeral homes, as the country continues its battle with an unprecedented wave of Covid-19 infections following its dismantling of severe pandemic restrictions.

entries.title: Vatican opens new investigation into 1983 disappearance of employee's daughter
entries.description: The Vatican has opened a new investigation into the disappearance of a 15-year-old daughter of one of its employees in 1983.

entries.title: Internet records for the husband of a missing Massachusetts woman show he searched for how to dispose of a body, sources say
entries.description: Police in the small coastal town of Cohasset, Massachusetts, are investigating the disappearance of a woman whose husband's internet records showed searches for how to dismember a body, sources tell CNN, and prosecutors say blood and a bloodied knife were found in the couple's basement.

entries.title: M&M's new packaging sparks 'culture war' outrage
entries.description: M&M'S is making a statement with its latest candy pack, which features an all-female set of characters — including Purple, its newest addition.

entries.title: CNN reporter lays out differences in Biden office classified documents and those found at Mar-a-Lago
entries.description: President Joe Biden's lawyers say they found classified government materials while closing out a Washington, DC-based office that Biden used as part of his relationship as an honorary professor for the University of Pennsylvania. CNN'S Paula Reid reports.

entries.title: How pioneering yacht Maiden overcame 'the real last bastion of male dominance' and empowered women around the world
entries.description: More than three decades since its pioneering, round-the-world voyage, the Maiden racing yacht is again sailing the high seas -- and changing the lives of young women in the process.

entries.title: Lawsuit over 1968 teenage nude scenes requires a rethink of 'Romeo and Juliet'
entries.description: Being a teenager means being vulnerable -- physically and emotionally besieged by adolescent hormones and the confusion of no longer being a child but not yet being fully an adult. It's a time many of us wince to recall, and one I wouldn't want to undertake again.

entries.title: 'A world rapidly warming': The past eight years were the eight warmest on record for planet
entries.description: The last eight years have been the eight warmest on record as the growing concentration of heat-trapping gases in the atmosphere pushes global temperatures toward a dangerous tipping point, a new report shows.

entries.title: Asian stocks enter bull market as investors bet on China
entries.description: Stocks in Asia are starting 2023 in a bull market. Investors have been cheered by China's pivot away from its zero-Covid policy, the ending of its crackdown on tech companies and Beijing's renewed commitment to growing the world's second biggest economy.

entries.title: Ellen DeGeneres posts video of flash flood near Montecito home
entries.description: Santa Barbara County was hit with severe rainfall turning streets into rivers, toppling trees, shuttering major roadways and prompting numerous water rescues. Emergency services responded to more than 200 incident calls. The entire town of Montecito, California, was told to evacuate.

entries.title: What Brazil lost after Bolsonaro supporters rioted in Brasilia
entries.description: Brazil's flag has a phrase etched in the middle of its blue, star-studded globe: "Order and Progress." The same flag was omnipresent as supporters of former president Jair Bolsonaro stormed the nation's capital, some donning it like a cape as they attacked government buildings, others using it as a towel to wipe away the tear gas fired by security forces to contain the crowds.

entries.title: Inside plans for Copenhagen's divisive artificial storm-absorbing peninsula
entries.description: In January 2022,  a team of developers, architects and environmental consultants began work on a 50-year project that — if completed — will become one of Denmark's most ambitious and controversial infrastructure schemes to date: A 271-acre man-made peninsula devised to shield its capital, Copenhagen, from rising sea levels.

entries.title: Pizza Hut is bringing back a fan favorite from the '90s
entries.description: Pizza Hut is bringing back a fan favorite after a nearly 25-year hiatus.

entries.title: Biden tries to stay focused on Mexico City summit after revelation that classified documents were found in his private office
entries.description: President Joe Biden is facing sharp new questions about his handling of classified documents as he prepares for a summit with the leaders of the US' neighboring nations.

entries.title: Russian artillery fire down nearly 75%, US officials say, in latest sign of struggles for Moscow
entries.description: As Russia's invasion of Ukraine enters its 11th month, US and Ukrainian officials tell CNN that Russia's artillery fire is down dramatically from its wartime high, in some places by as much as 75 percent.

entries.title: Biden administration prepares more measures to curb border crossings, keep migrants from journeying to the US
entries.description: The Biden administration will roll out additional measures during Tuesday's North American Leaders' Summit in a desperate bid to keep migrants from journeying to the US southern border.

entries.title: From feminist pioneers to putting pros, the historic journey of the world's oldest ladies golf club
entries.description: Who would you back to sink a putt to save your life? Tiger Woods? Jack Nicklaus? Ben Crenshaw?

entries.title: Russia putting greatest effort into capturing town near Bakhmut, Zelensky says
French football president apologises for 'awkward remarks' on Zidane after backlash
entries.description: France Football Federation (FFF) president Noel Le Graet apologised to Zinedine Zidane on Monday after his comments on the former Real Madrid coach drew the ire of players, politicians and even the Spanish club.

entries.title: Melbourne Victory hit with record sanctions after ugly pitch invasion
entries.description: Melbourne Victory FC has been fined $310,000 (AUS$ 450,000) and hit with a number of sanctions by Football Australia (FA) after the ugly scenes that forced its derby match against Melbourne City to be abandoned in December.

entries.title: Liposuction overtakes breast augmentation as most popular cosmetic surgery
entries.description: Liposuction has overtaken breast augmentation as the world's most popular form of cosmetic surgery amid growing concern about the implants' links to cancer, according to newly published data from the International Society of Aesthetic Plastic Surgery (ISAPS).

entries.title: Thousands urged to flee their homes as storm wallops California, closing down roads, prompting water rescues and leaving 1 dead
entries.description: A powerful storm battering California has forced thousands to evacuate -- including an entire community -- and prompted dozens of water rescues as floodwater inundated roadways, swept away vehicles and caused widespread damage.

entries.title: Why it could be happy hour for Dubai tourists after alcohol tax is scrapped
entries.description: Dubai is a huge draw for visitors, attracting almost 13 million international tourists from January to November 2022. They arrive from across the globe to tan on the sandy beaches, shop in the extravagant malls, eat in the world-class restaurants, and even to drink in the city's many bars.

entries.title: Damar Hamlin is beginning the next phase of recovery in a Buffalo hospital a week after cardiac arrest on the field
entries.description: A week after NFL star Damar Hamlin suffered a cardiac arrest on the field during a game in Ohio, the Bills' safety was back in Buffalo, New York, where he is continuing the next stage of recovery Tuesday.

entries.title: 'History might repeat itself': Chinese ambassador warns Australia to be wary of Japan
entries.description: China's ambassador to Australia says Canberra should be wary of its relationship with Japan, reminding them that Japanese troops attacked Australia during World War II and could do the same again.

entries.title: Chinese rocket startup Galactic Energy sends five satellites into space
entries.description: Galactic Energy, a rocket startup in China, launched five satellites into orbit on Monday, boosting the private company's ambition to become the Chinese rival to SpaceX.

entries.title: Onions are so expensive in the Philippines they're being smuggled into the country
entries.description: From salads to stews, the humble onion is a key ingredient in nearly every Filipino dish. But now, the vegetable costs almost three times more than chicken in the Philippines.

entries.title: China stops issuing short-term visas for South Koreans in retaliation for travel restrictions
entries.description: Chinese authorities have stopped issuing short-term visas to South Korean citizens in the country's first retaliation against Covid entry restrictions on arrivals from China.

entries.title: Protesters clash with police at Covid-19 test factory in China
entries.description: Workers from the Zybio Inc. factory in Chongqing protested and clashed with police after their managers abruptly told them to go on holiday early, effectively terminating their employment.

entries.title: Russian forces claim capturing east Ukraine village near key city of Bakhmut
Former US fighter pilot arrested in Australia over China training allegations 'singled out,' lawyer says
entries.description: The lawyer for former US Marine Corps pilot Daniel Duggan said he was "singled out" for extradition to the United States to face charges of training Chinese military fliers, even though other Australians provided military services to foreign states.

entries.title: See families eagerly reunite in China after Covid lockdowns lifted
entries.description: Thousands of travelers crossed mainland China's borders for joyful reunions and long-awaited journeys as authorities relaxed restrictions that had both separated families and isolated the world's most populous country for nearly three years.  CNN's Selina Wang reports.

entries.title: Classified documents from Biden's time as VP discovered in private office
Analysis: Biden document revelations are a gift for Trump and deepen Garland's nightmare
entries.description: Republicans seized on revelations that several classified documents from Joe Biden's time as vice president were found in his former private office to create cover for former President Donald Trump's hoarding of secret records.

entries.title: Brazil's Lula criticizes police for protesters' breach of government buildings
How do you harness an epic amount of rain in a water-scarce state? Let it flood, scientists say
entries.description: California has gone from extreme drought to extreme flooding in a matter of days. On Monday, 90% of the state's population was under a flood watch as another round of storms rolled through. Yet it was just last week when several counties in the state were experiencing the exact opposite -- exceptional drought, which the US Drought Monitor considers the most severe category.

entries.title: Fisher-Price reminds consumers of 2019 recall of Rock 'n Play Sleepers after more deaths
entries.description: Fisher-Price has reannounced its 2019 recall of the Rock 'n Play Sleepers on Monday after at least eight infant deaths occurred after the initial recall, according to the Consumer Product Safety Commission.

entries.title: War game projects possible outcomes for US in a war with China over Taiwan
entries.description: According to a prominent independent Washington think tank, which conducted war game simulations of a possible conflict, projected possible outcomes of a Chinese invasion of Taiwan in 2026. CNN's Oren Liebermann has more.

entries.title: Where Chinese tourists are flying this year
entries.description: The day has come: China has reopened its borders to some travelers for the first time since the onset of the coronavirus pandemic in early 2020.

entries.title: More than 1,000 arrested in Brazil protests, justice minister says
House approves rules package for new Congress in key test for McCarthy
entries.description: The House is expected to vote Monday evening on the rules package for the 118th Congress, in what will mark the first test of House Speaker Kevin McCarthy's slim Republican majority after he made key concessions to GOP hardliners to win the gavel.

entries.title: Former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro has been hospitalized, according to his wife
Classified documents found at Biden private office. Hear what he said about Trump Mar-a-Lago documents
entries.description: Several classified documents from President Joe Biden's time as vice president were discovered last fall in a private office, Biden's attorneys acknowledged. CNN's Evan Perez reports.

entries.title: Giuliani subpoenaed amid investigation into Trump's fundraising
entries.description: Special counsel Jack Smith's team has subpoenaed Donald Trump's former attorney Rudy Giuliani, asking him to turn over records to a federal grand jury as part of an investigation into the former president's fundraising following the 2020 election, according to a person familiar with the subpoena.
